rd%20for%20vertical%20flight.%20Its%20stub%20wings%2C%20which%20could%20be%20folded%20to%20save%20space%2C%20had%20four%20hardpoints%20enabling%20the%20jet%20to%20carry%20about%202%2C000%20pounds%20of%20ordnance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%20231%20Yak-38s%20were%20eventually%20built.%20Despite%20its%20novelty%2C%20however%2C%20the%20jet%20was%20mostly%20a%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20Soviet%20navy%20Yak-38%20aircraft%20carrier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6553b5284ca513d824291d25%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYak-38%20jets%20on%20the%20deck%20of%20Soviet%20Kiev-class%20carrier%20Minsk%20in%20November%201982.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20prone%20to%20mechanical%20issues%2C%20especially%20in%20hot%20and%20humid%20environments.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Kiev's%20first%20cruise%20in%201976%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20only%20one%20of%20its%20six%20Yak-38s%20was%20still%20operational.%20The%20jet%20also%20had%20trouble%20with%20its%20automatic%20ejection%20system%2C%20which%20activated%20by%20accident%20on%20multiple%20occasions%20and%20wrecked%20the%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Yak-38%20had%20many%20other%20shortcomings.%20Its%20range%2C%20payload%2C%20and%20speed%20were%20less%20than%20that%20of%20rival%20militaries'%20aircraft.%20Even%20the%20updated%20Yak-36M%2C%20with%20a%20longer%20range%20and%20double%20the%20payload%2C%20was%20underpowered%20compared%20to%20NATO%20carrier%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inefficiency%20of%20the%20Yak-38's%20lift%20engines%20meant%20the%20jet%20rarely%20took%20off%20vertically%2C%20as%20it%20consumed%20too%20much%20fuel%20and%20limited%20the%20jet's%20already%20small%20payload.%20The%20Yak-38%20didn't%20have%20its%20own%20radar%2C%20meaning%20its%20pilot%20was%20reliant%20on%20visual%20sightings%20or%20on%20other%20Soviet%20forces%20for%20guidance.%20The%20jet%20could%20carry%20Kh-23%20anti-ship%20missiles%2C%20but%20since%20it%20was%20a%20single-seater%2C%20the%20pilot%20would%20have%20to%20fly%20the%20jet%20and%20guide%20the%20missile%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Yak-38%20only%20saw%20combat%20in%20landlocked%20Afghanistan.%20At%20least%20four%20Yak-38s%20operated%20alongside%20other%20Soviet%20jets%20from%20a%20base%20in%20the%20country's%20southwest%20in%201980.%20While%20it%20conducted%20a%20number%20of%20airstrikes%20during%20its%20month-long%20deployment%2C%20the%20jet%20still%20struggled%20with%20the%20heat%20and%20dust%2C%20and%20its%20performance%20was%20not%20particularly%20noteworthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoviet%20leaders%20decided%20against%20further%20upgrades%20and%20retired%20the%20Yak-38%20shortly%20after%20the%20Soviet%20collapsed%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESu-33%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Su-33%20fighter%20takeoff%20Admiral%20Kuznetsov%20aircraft%20carrier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F613fab53261771001825e516%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221288%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Su-33%20takes%20off%20of%20the%20Admiral%20Kuznetsov%20as%20it%20sails%20off%20the%20Syrian%20coast%20in%20January%202017.%3Cp%3EAndrei%20Luzik%5C%5CTASS%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20first%20Kiev-class%20carriers%20and%20Yak-38s%20began%20to%20enter%20service%20in%20the%20mid-1970s%2C%20the%20Soviets%20were%20planning%20their%20replacements.%20By%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Soviet%20military's%20thinking%20about%20the%20value%20of%20sea%20control%20and%20naval%20air%20dominance%20had%20changed%2C%20and%20its%20commanders%20saw%20that%20V%2FSTOL%20jets%20and%20the%20Yak-38%20in%20particular%20had%20limited%20utility%20for%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Soviets%20sought%20a%20larger%20carrier%20and%20a%20jet%20capable%20of%20conventional%20takeoffs%20and%20landings%20%E2%80%94%20like%20those%20of%20the%20major%20NATO%20powers%20%E2%80%94%20to%20provide%20greater%20range%20and%20payload%20and%20more%20reliability%20in%20dogfights.%20The%20result%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.militarytoday.com%2Fnavy%2Fkuznetsov_class.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKuznetsov-class%20carrier%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.militarytoday.com%2Faircraft%2Fsu_33.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESu-33%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Su-33%20was%20effectively%20a%20naval%20variant%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.militarytoday.com%2Faircraft%2Fsukhoi_su27_flanker.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESu-27%3C%2Fa%3E%20air-superiority%20fighter%20with%20several%20differences%2C%20including%20a%20reinforced%20undercarriage%20and%20landing%20gear%20for%20carrier%20landings%2C%20forward%20canards%20to%20reduce%20takeoff%20distance%2C%20a%20larger%20wing%20area%20for%20extra%20lift%2C%20foldable%20wings%2C%20and%20more%20powerful%20engines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Su-33%20fighter%20landing%20on%20Admiral%20Kuznetsov%20aircraft%20carrier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F613fab54261771001825e519%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Su-33%20lands%20on%20Admiral%20Kuznetsov%20as%20it%20sails%20off%20the%20Syrian%20coast%20in%20November%202016.%3Cp%3EAndrei%20Luzik%5C%5CTASS%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20jet%20had%20a%20top%20speed%20of%20more%20than%201%2C400%20mph%20and%20a%20range%20of%20over%202%2C000%20miles%2C%20along%20with%20a%2030mm%20cannon%20and%2012%20hardpoints%20that%20could%20carry%2014%2C000%20pounds%20of%20ordnance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20jet's%20improvements%20over%20the%20Yak-38%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-plans-for-su33-as-carrier-based-fighter-fell-apart-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20was%20also%20of%20limited%20effectiveness%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Because%20the%20jet%20was%20exceptionally%20large%2C%20the%20Kuznetsov%2C%20which%20was%20smaller%20than%20US%20carriers%2C%20couldn't%20carry%20many%20of%20them.%20The%20jet's%20size%20also%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20move%20around%20on%20the%20carrier.%20The%20Su-33%20was%20also%20meant%20to%20be%20capable%20of%20ground-attack%20missions%2C%20but%20its%20takeoff%20weight%2C%20and%20thus%20the%20weaponry%20it%20could%20carry%2C%20were%20limited%20by%20Kuznetsov's%20ski-jump%20ramp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Su-33%20didn't%20enter%20service%20until%20after%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20and%20only%20about%2022%20were%20built.%20Three%20have%20been%20lost%20in%20crashes%2C%20and%20only%2017%20are%20believed%20to%20still%20be%20in%20service%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMiG-29K%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MiG%2029K%20aircraft%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20indian%20navy%20aircraft%20carrier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F57dab3bcb0ef97f0288b5aa2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22586%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20MiG-29K%20lands%20on%20Indian%20navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20in%202014.%3Cp%3EIndian%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Sukhoi%20design%20firm%20was%20working%20on%20the%20Su-33%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20Mikoyan%20Design%20Bureau%20was%20working%20on%20its%20own%20carrier%20aircraft%2C%20the%20MiG-29K%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcombat-jets-russia-and-ukraine-are-using-in-ukraine-war-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enaval%20variant%20of%20the%20MiG-29%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWork%20on%20the%20MiG-29K%20was%20halted%20in%201991%20when%20the%20Russian%20navy%20selected%20the%20Su-33%20for%20its%20carriers%2C%20but%20the%20project%20was%20revived%20in%202004%20for%20the%20Indian%20navy%2C%20which%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinterest.org%2Fblog%2Fbuzz%2Fall-reasons-why-india-hates-aircraft-carrier-it-bought-russia-92076%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquiring%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Kiev-class%20carrier%20Admiral%20Gorhskov%20from%20Russia%2C%20and%20wanted%20the%20jet%20for%20the%20carrier's%20air%20wing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20top%20speed%20of%20about%201%2C300%20mph%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20carry%209%2C900%20pounds%20of%20ordnance%2C%20the%20MiG-29K%20was%20better%20suited%20for%20ground%20strikes%20than%20the%20Su-33.%20India%20also%20chose%20the%20MiG-29K%20because%20its%20air%20force%20already%20operated%20the%20MiG-29%20and%20was%20familiar%20with%20the%20airframe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Indian%20navy%20MiG-29%20fighter%20jet%20aircraft%20carrier%20INS%20Vikrant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63f7b6e86e91cc0018df5683%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20MiG-29%20aboard%20the%20aircraft%20carrier%20INS%20Vikrant%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3EARUN%20SANKAR%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20placed%20two%20orders%2C%20in%202004%20and%202010%2C%20for%2045%20aircraft%20and%20related%20equipment%20for%20%242.2%20billion.%20Its%20first%20MiG-29Ks%20were%20delivered%20in%202009%2C%20and%20the%20first%20squadron%20became%20operational%20in%202013.%20The%20MiG-29K%20also%20underperformed%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202016%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fwebroot%2Fuploads%2Fdownload_audit_report%2F2016%2FUnion_Defence_Services_Navy_and_Coast_Guard_Report_No_17_of_2016.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20India's%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20said%20that%20between%202009%20and%202015%2C%20the%20MiG-29Ks%20that%20had%20been%20delivered%20were%20only%20available%20for%20service%20between%2015.93%25%20and%2047.14%25%20of%20the%20time.%20In%20addition%20to%20issues%20with%20the%20jet's%20airframe%20and%20avionics%2C%20the%20report%20said%2062%25%20of%20the%20engines%20delivered%20by%20Russia%20had%20been%20withdrawn%20from%20service%20or%20were%20rejected%20because%20of%20defects%20and%20deficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20five%20of%20the%20Indian%20navy's%20MiG-29Ks%20were%20lost%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.janes.com%2Fdefence-news%2Fnews-detail%2Findian-navy-reports-crash-of-fifth-mig-29k-in-four-years%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOf%2520the%2520five%2520MiG%252D29K%2Cduring%2520the%2520last%252010%2520years.%26amp%3Btext%3Din%252Dfour%252Dyears-%2CAn%2520Indian%2520Navy%2520Mikoyan%252DGurevich%2520MiG%252D29K%2520crashed%2520in%2520the%2CArabian%2520Sea%2520on%252012%2520October.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrashes%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%202018%20and%202022%20%E2%80%94%20a%20far%20higher%20rate%20than%20for%20the%20Indian%20air%20force's%20MiG-29s.%20The%20problems%20were%20compounded%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20was%20wholly%20reliant%20on%20Russia%20for%20major%20support%20issues%2C%20as%20Moscow%20refused%20to%20transfer%20jet-engine%20technology%20or%20allow%20India%20to%20build%20its%20own%20MiG-29Ks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20navy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense-aerospace.com%2Findia-says-mig-29-serviceability-issues-now-solved-admiral%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018%20that%20all%20serviceability%20issues%20had%20been%20resolved.%20It%20even%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forb