nt's%20aircraft%20elevator%2C%20and%20eventually%20to%20use%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftwin-engine-carrier-based-fighter-for-navy-could-be-inducted-by-2031-32%2Farticle66124792.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edomestically%20developed%3C%2Fa%3E%20carrier-based%20jet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20MiG-29K%20program%20was%20restarted%20for%20India%2C%20Russia's%20navy%20ordered%2025%20of%20the%20jets%20in%202009%20to%20use%20aboard%20Kuznetsov.%20The%20fighter%20made%20its%20combat%20debut%20in%202016%2C%20flying%20from%20the%20carrier%20during%20a%20deployment%20to%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20the%20jet%20nor%20the%20ship%20emerged%20unscathed.%20In%20one%20incident%2C%20a%20MiG-29K%20broke%20the%20carrier's%20arresting%20cable%20during%20landing.%20As%20the%20crew%20cleared%20debris%20from%20the%20deck%2C%20another%20MiG-29K%20circling%20overhead%20crashed%20into%20the%20sea%20after%20its%20engines%20unexpectedly%20shut%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20had%20planned%20replace%20its%20Su-33s%20with%20MiG-29Ks%20but%20later%20decided%20that%20the%20MiGs%20would%20supplement%20its%20Su-33%20fleet%20instead.%20Since%20Kuznetsov%20began%20its%20refit%20in%20early%202017%2C%20however%2C%20no%20jet%20has%20flown%20from%20the%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-keeps-building-ineffective-jets-for-its-navy-aircraft-carriers-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700090581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F613facc02534ab0018540544%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-keeps-building-ineffective-jets-for-its-navy-aircraft-carriers-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20if%20Russia's%20sole%20aircraft%20carrier%20returns%20to%20service%20next%20year%2C%20it%20probably%20won't%20have%20a%20fully%20functioning%20air%20wing%20any%20time%20soon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Benjamin%20Brimelow)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-keeps-building-ineffective-jets-for-its-navy-aircraft-carriers-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Massive%20Amazon%20warehouses%20are%20used%20to%20ship%20and%20store%20open-box%2C%20refurbished%2C%20and%20returned%20products%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223111%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20warehouse%20with%20an%20Amazon%20truck%20in%20front%20of%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65548cf322cf74a573978345%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlbert%20Elliott%2C%20an%20Amazon%20warehouse%20worker%20in%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20recently%20started%20a%20second%20job%20as%20a%20janitor%20at%20a%20community%20college.%3Cp%3EEduardo%20Munoz%20Avarez%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAmazon%20operates%20nearly%20300%20warehouses%20worldwide%2C%20with%20some%20as%20large%20as%20a%20million%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAmazon%20Warehouse%20is%20also%20a%20feature%20on%20the%20Amazon%20website%20where%20customers%20can%20find%20deals%20on%20pre-owned%2C%20used%2C%20and%20open%20box%20products.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20starting%20out%20as%20an%20online%20book%20seller%20in%201994%2C%20today%20Amazon%20is%20nearly%20the%20largest%20retailer%20in%20the%20world%2C%20second%20only%20to%20Walmart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20Walmart%20operates%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20brick-and-mortar%20stores%20in%20two%20dozen%20countries%2C%20the%20core%20of%20Amazon's%20business%20is%20online%2C%20shipping%20most%20of%20its%20products%20directly%20to%20homes%20and%20businesses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20that%20requires%20a%20substantial%20warehousing%20and%20distribution%20network.%20In%201997%2C%20Amazon%20had%20a%20single%2093%2C000-square-foot%20warehouse%20in%20Seattle.%20Today%2C%20the%20retailer%20operates%20110%20warehouses%20in%20the%20US%20and%20another%20185%20internationally%2C%20though%20the%20size%20dwarfs%20that%20original%20warehouse%20with%20some%20as%20large%20as%20a%20million%20square%20feet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20does%20Amazon%20choose%20warehouse%20locations%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20company%20has%20grown%2C%20it%20has%20continued%20to%20add%20warehouses%20in%20strategic%20locations%20throughout%20the%20US%20and%20around%20the%20world.%20The%20company%20considers%20a%20variety%20of%20factors%20when%20choosing%20where%20to%20place%20warehouses%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-fulfillment-center%5C%22%3EAmazon%20fulfillment%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20factors%20contribute%20to%20location%20decisions%2C%20though%20these%20are%20among%20the%20most%20important%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EProximity%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Amazon%20chooses%20locations%20based%20on%20customer%20proximity%2C%20positioning%20warehouses%20close%20to%20major%20population%20centers%20to%20minimize%20shipping%20and%20delivery%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETransportation%20infrastructure%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20It's%20also%20important%20for%20fulfillment%20centers%20to%20have%20close%20proximity%20to%20mature%20transportation%20networks%20including%20airports%2C%20seaports%2C%20rail%20lines%2C%20highways%2C%20and%20surface%20roads.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELand%20cost%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Because%20Amazon%20warehouses%20are%20so%20large%2C%20with%20some%20as%20much%20as%20a%20million%20square%20feet%2C%20land%20cost%20is%20an%20important%20consideration%20in%20the%20calculus%20of%20choosing%20a%20location.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Amazon%20takes%20into%20consideration%20proximity%20to%20suppliers%20and%20vendors%20to%20streamline%20the%20brand's%20supply%20chain%2C%20local%20regulatory%20issues%20that%20could%20impact%20the%20retailer's%20ability%20to%20operate%20effectively%2C%20environmental%20concerns%20(such%20as%20a%20location's%20ability%20to%20help%20Amazon%20meet%20its%20goals%20around%20reducing%20its%20carbon%20footprint)%2C%20and%20risk%20mitigation%20(regional%20susceptibility%20to%20natural%20disasters%20or%20geopolitical%20instability%20could%20deter%20Amazon%20from%20choosing%20a%20particular%20location.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20Amazon%20warehouses%20is%20a%20moving%20target%20as%20the%20retailer%20adds%20new%20locations%20in%20response%20to%20demand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20types%20of%20sellers%20work%20with%20Amazon%20warehouses%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Amazon's%20retail%20power%20comes%20from%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-fba%5C%22%3EFulfilled%20By%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20program%2C%20commonly%20called%20FBA.%20Small%20businesses%20commonly%20use%20the%20FBA%20program%20to%20sell%20products%20on%20the%20Amazon%20website%20and%20Amazon%20fulfills%20orders%20on%20their%20behalf%20automatically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBA%20program%20is%20designed%20for%20sellers%20who%20want%20to%20leverage%20the%20scale%20of%20Amazon%20for%20their%20own%20inventory.%20Amazon%20offers%20variations%20for%20both%20individual%20sellers%20%E2%80%94%20people%20who%20sell%20infrequently%20or%20on%20a%20small%20scale%20%E2%80%94%20and%20professional%20sellers%20who%20work%20in%20bulk%20or%20larger%20volume.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20seller%20can%20work%20with%20Amazon%20as%20long%20as%20they%20are%20able%20to%20successfully%20complete%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-seller%5C%22%3EAmazon%20seller%3C%2Fa%3E%20account%2C%20shop%20products%20to%20Amazon%20warehouses%20as%20needed%2C%20and%20meet%20basic%20product%20requirements.%20The%20products%20must%20obviously%20be%20legal%20to%20sell%20in%20the%20US%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20fall%20into%20one%20of%20about%2020%20categories%20like%20beauty%2C%20books%2C%20business%20products%2C%20electronics%2C%20clothing%2C%20jewelry%2C%20home%20and%20garden%2C%20and%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20exceptions.%20Within%20each%20category%2C%20Amazon%20prohibits%20the%20sale%20of%20certain%20items%2C%20and%20maintains%20a%20master%20list%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsellercentral.amazon.com%2Fhelp%2Fhub%2Freference%2Fexternal%2F200164330%3Fref%3Dmpbc_200277040_cont_200164330%26locale%3Den-US%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestricted%20products%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20do%20I%20know%20which%20Amazon%20warehouse%20to%20ship%20to%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20part%20of%20the%20FBA%20program%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20know%20where%20to%20ship%20your%20products%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20there%20are%20hundreds%20to%20choose%20from.%20The%20simple%20answer%3A%20Create%20your%20shipping%20plan%20on%20your%20Amazon%20Sellers%20Account%20website%20after%20manufacturing%20is%20complete%20and%20you%20are%20ready%20to%20ship.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20your%20shipping%20plan%20by%20choosing%20the%20%3Cstrong%3EListing%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esection%20after%20clicking%20%3Cstrong%3EInventory%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20your%20Sellers%20account%2C%20and%20Amazon%20tells%20you%20where%20to%20ship%20your%20products.%20If%20your%20shipment%20is%20large%2C%20Amazon%20might%20even%20divide%20the%20shipment%20between%20two%20or%20more%20warehouses.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20does%20an%20Amazon%20warehouse%20carry%20that%20a%20fulfillment%20center%20doesn't%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20generally%20uses%20the%20term%20fulfillment%20center%20to%20refer%20to%20its%20large%20warehouses.%20That's%20because%20rather%20than%20simply%20warehousing%20products%2C%20Amazon%20uses%20the%20facilities%20to%20fulfill%20customer%20orders.%20They're%20distribution%20centers%20where%20employees%20sort%2C%20retrieve%2C%20pack%2C%20and%20ship%20orders%20directly%20to%20customers.%20At%20many%20fulfillment%20centers%2C%20human%20associates%20work%20in%20concert%20with%20equipment%20that%20includes%20autonomous%20robots%20to%20quickly%20process%20orders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20Amazon%20warehouses%20work%20this%20way%2C%20though%20%E2%80%94%20the%20retailer%20also%20operates%20much%20smaller%20warehouses%20that%20cater%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20Amazon%20Now%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-fresh%5C%22%3EAmazon%20Fresh%3C%2Fa%3E%20stores%2C%20for%20example.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20Amazon%20Warehouse%20on%20Amazon.com%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20be%20confused%20with%20Amazon's%20network%20of%20fulfillment%20centers%20around%20the%20world%2C%20Amazon%20Warehouse%20is%20a%20special%20section%20of%20the%20Amazon%20website%20where%20customers%20can%20find%20deals%20on%20pre-owned%2C%20used%2C%20and%20open%20box%20products.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EItems%20listed%20in%20Amazon%20Warehouse%20are%20generally%20returned%20products.%20Items%20returned%20to%20Amazon%20are%20inspected%20with%20a%20quality%20check%20and%20given%20a%20grade%20based%20on%20their%20physical%20condition%2C%20packaging%20quality%2C%20missing%20accessories%2C%20and%20other%20criteria.%20They're%20labeled%20with%20a%20condition%20%E2%80%94%20Like%20New%2C%20Very%20Good%2C%20Good%2C%20and%20Acceptable%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20placed%20for%20sale%20on%20the%20website.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EItems%20sold%20on%20the%20Amazon%20Warehouse%20website%20are%20covered%20under%20Amazon's%20normal%20return%20policy%20so%20that%20purchases%20can%20be%20returned%20for%20a%20replacement%20or%20refund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-warehouse%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Inside