ider.com%2Ftarget-syndrome-why-we-always-buy-things-we-dont-need-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunplanned%20purchases%20that%20make%20a%20Target%20run%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Target%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20one%20thing%20that%20we've%20seen%20is%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20people%20are%20making%20choices%20and%20they%20might%20have%20constraints%20with%20their%20budget%2C%20the%20motivation%20to%20buy%20is%20really%20'Is%20this%20going%20to%20add%20value%20to%20my%20life%3F%20Is%20this%20something%20intriguing%20and%20feels%20relevant%20or%20fashion%20forward%20or%20is%20really%20for%20me%3F'%26quot%3B%20Target%20Chief%20Growth%20Officer%20Christina%20Hennington%20said%20on%20the%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20revenge%20spending%20is%20tapering%20off%2C%20the%20company%20is%20also%20seeing%20customers%20delay%20some%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20year%2C%20we've%20seen%20more%20and%20more%20consumers%20delaying%20their%20spending%20until%20the%20last%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20Cornell%20said.%C2%A0%26quot%3BGuests%20who%20previously%20bought%20sweatshirts%20or%20denim%20in%20August%20or%20September%20are%20deciding%20to%20wait%20until%20the%20weather%20turns%20cold%20before%20making%20a%20purchase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20clear%20indication%20of%20the%20pressures%20they're%20facing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20pointing%20to%20food%20prices%20remaining%20at%20a%20stubborn%2025%25%20above%20their%202020%20levels.%20%26quot%3BIt%20all%20puts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-consumer-spending-credit-card-debt-delinquencies-retail-hiring-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epressure%20on%20discretionary%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthank-the-american-retail-consumer-for-the-soft-landing-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20re