%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20boomer%20who%20moved%20to%20Texas%20and%20was%20able%20to%20retire%20early.%20Almost%20everything%20is%20cheaper%20here%2C%20but%20the%20bugs%20and%20snakes%20are%20wild.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20posing%20with%20a%20glass%20of%20wine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655519d336d588dc55d10c69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJayne%20Jordan%20moved%20from%20Corona%2C%20California%2C%20to%20Azle%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%20August.%3Cp%3EJayne%20Jordan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJayne%20Jordan%2C%2061%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20moved%20to%20Azle%2C%20Texas%2C%2030%20minutes%20from%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20in%20August.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20cost%20of%20their%20housing%20was%20so%20much%20less%20than%20in%20California%20that%20Jordan%20was%20able%20to%20retire%20early.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJordan%20said%20most%20things%20are%20cheaper%20in%20Texas%2C%20especially%20gas%20and%20groceries%2C%20but%20not%20property%20taxes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jayne%20Jordan%2C%2061%2C%20about%20her%20decision%20to%20move%20from%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20area%20to%20Azle%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%20August.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20knew%20we%20were%20going%20to%20move%20out%20of%20California%20to%20retire%20somewhere%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20sure%20where.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20is%20a%20teacher%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Irvine%2C%20which%20is%20an%20affluent%20area%20of%20California%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20works%20for%20the%20county.%20They%20could%20never%20buy%20a%20house%20in%20California%20%E2%80%94%20they%20couldn't%20even%20save%20up%20for%20a%20down%20payment%20because%20rents%20are%20so%20ridiculous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20plan%20was%20to%20move%20to%20Texas%2C%20and%20we%20just%20decided%20to%20follow%20along%20and%20we%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20it%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20coming%20in%20June%20when%20school's%20out%2C%20but%20we%20found%20a%20house%20the%20last%20time%20we%20came%2C%20which%20was%20in%20the%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20sold%20our%20house%20in%20Corona%20in%20four%20days%20for%20%24850%2C000%2C%20and%20we%20purchased%20our%20home%20in%20Azle%20for%20%24587%2C000%20with%20a%20%2410%2C000%20incentive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20bank%20on%20our%20house%2C%20so%20we%20have%20a%20very%20minimal%20mortgage%20%E2%80%94%20we%20could%20have%20paid%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20at%20the%20retirement%20age%2C%20so%20I%20was%20able%20to%20retire%20and%20not%20have%20to%20work%20anymore.%20I%20couldn't%20have%20done%20that%20in%20California%20for%20at%20least%20another%20couple%20years%2C%20so%20it%20was%20a%20win-win%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20left%20California%20because%20the%20traffic%20was%20too%20much%2C%20but%20Texas%20has%20its%20downsides%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20hated%20the%20traffic%2C%20smog%2C%20and%20crime.%20We%20were%20in%20an%20area%20in%20the%20Inland%20Empire%20where%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20wildfires.%20We%20were%20evacuated%20a%20couple%20of%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scare%20of%20the%20fires%20and%20the%20traffic%20congestion%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20just%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20traffic%20in%20Texas%2C%20but%20not%20where%20we%20live%2C%20so%20if%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20drive%20in%20it%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20big%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20living%20in%20an%201%2C800-square-foot%20house%20in%20California%20and%20we%20really%20wanted%20more%20land.%20This%20one%20is%202%2C262%20square%20feet%2C%20so%20the%20house%20isn't%20huge%2C%20but%20it's%20on%20an%20acre.%20It's%20gorgeous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20want%20a%20nice%20big%20pool%2C%20so%20it%20was%20always%20in%20our%20little%20future%20dream%20to%20retire%20and%20get%20out%20of%20the%20hub%20of%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Azle%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20trees%20and%20deer%20and%20everything%20all%20around.%20But%20if%20you%20drive%20out%20of%20our%20subdivision%20and%20go%20down%20the%20street%20you're%20in%20civilization%20with%20restaurants%20and%20stuff.%20So%20it's%20the%20perfect%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20two-story%20house%20with%20a%20big%20green%20yard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655517244ca513d8242a1237%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJordan's%20new%20home%20in%20Azle%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EJayne%20Jordan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20bugs.%20The%20first%20thing%20we%20did%20when%20we%20moved%20in%20was%20get%20an%20extermination%20service%20that%20comes%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%20to%20spray%20for%20bugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20things%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20driving%20us%20crazy%20%E2%80%94%20is%20there's%20these%20little%20stickers%20in%20the%20grass%20and%20they're%20really%20hard%20to%20get%20rid%20of.%20So%20when%20the%20grandkids%20were%20here%2C%20they%20had%20these%20stickers%20stuck%20to%20their%20clothes%2C%20and%20if%20you%20step%20on%20them%2C%20they%20really%20hurt.%20So%20we're%20trying%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20all%20these%20stickers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20haven't%20had%20any%20snake%20encounters.%20The%20builders%20are%20saying%20they%20didn't%20see%20any%20snakes%20when%20they%20were%20building%20the%20homes%2C%20however%2C%20the%20guy%20across%20the%20street%20from%20us%20killed%20two%20copperheads%20in%20his%20backyard%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEverything%20(except%20property%20taxes)%20is%20cheaper%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGas%20here%20is%20%242.53.%20In%20California%2C%20we%20were%20paying%20%245.89%20up%20to%20%246%20a%20gallon.%20So%20that's%20the%20difference%20in%20gas.%20Groceries%20here%20are%20cheaper%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20state%20income%20tax%20in%20Texas%2C%20so%20my%20husband%20already%20made%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20just%20from%20not%20paying%20state%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20property%20tax%20is%20higher%20in%20Texas%20than%20in%20California%2C%20so%20that%20eats%20a%20part%20of%20that%20away%2C%20but%20not%20hugely.%20It's%20not%20a%20ton%20more%20than%20we%20were%20paying%20in%20California%2C%20just%20a%20little%20bit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20a%20tree-lined%20street%20from%20inside%20of%20a%20car.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655516db4ca513d8242a11ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20tree-lined%20street%20in%20Texas.%3Cp%3EJayne%20Jordan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20live%20in%20a%20great%20neighborhood%2C%20we've%20met%20a%20ton%20of%20our%20neighbors%2C%20and%20pretty%20much%20everybody%20that%20we%20have%20encountered%20in%20Texas%20are%20just%20super%20nice%20and%20friendly%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20California's%20kind%20of%20snotty%20people.%20You%20get%20used%20to%20it%2C%20but%20people%20in%20Texas%20are%20just%20far%20nicer%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20miss%20some%20of%20the%20weather.%20California%20had%20pretty%20good%20weather%20most%20of%20the%20time.%20When%20we%20first%20got%20to%20Texas%2C%20it%20was%20really%20hot%2C%20so%20we%20really%20got%20to%20experience%20the%20summer%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20don't%20regret%20anything.%20Nothing%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20great.%20We%20haven't%20had%20a%20bad%20thought%20about%20it%20since%20we've%20been%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-texas-b