horToDOM%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frgupta.substack.com%2Fp%2Freflections-on-the-israel-palestine%23footnote-1-138856401%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E1%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20difficult%20not%20to%20have%20a%20strong%20visceral%20reaction%20to%20such%20suffering%3B%20however%2C%20I%20am%20conscious%20of%20my%20distance%20from%20this%20conflict%20in%20which%20all%20principal%20stakeholders%20have%20personally%20experienced%20loss%20at%20one%20time%20or%20the%20other.%20Some%20tentativeness%20is%20only%20fitting.%20I%20am%20not%20going%20to%20write%20about%20what%20was%20done%20or%20what%20should%20be%20done%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%20very%20many%20columns%20and%20podcasts%20from%20more%20relevant%20people%20to%20read%20and%20listen%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20and%20large%2C%20the%20ones%20I%20most%20agree%20with%20converge%20on%20the%20following%20points%3A%20what%20Hamas%20did%20was%20an%20act%20of%20terrorism%20deserving%20of%20unequivocal%20condemnation%3B%20any%20meaningful%20discussion%20must%20be%20situated%20in%20the%20context%20and%20history%20of%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20which%20includes%20not%20just%20Jewish%20persecution%20but%20also%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20their%20continued%20oppression%3B%20Israel%20cannot%20not%20go%20after%20Hamas%2C%20not%20least%20because%20the%20primary%20responsibility%20of%20any%20state%20is%20to%20provide%20security%20to%20its%20citizenry%20and%20its%20geopolitical%20context%20which%20requires%20establishing%20some%20manner%20of%20deterrence%20for%20such%20acts%3B%20but%20going%20after%20Hamas%20means%20targeted%20action%20instead%20of%20this%20unconscionable%20bombing%20of%20the%20entire%20Gaza%20strip%20which%20is%20leading%20to%20unacceptable%20civilian%20casualties%3B%20ultimately%2C%20the%20only%20lasting%20resolution%20will%20be%20political%2C%20which%20affords%20Palestinians%20dignity%20and%20agency%20instead%20of%20treating%20this%20as%20a%20security%20issue%20in%20perpetuity%3B%20and%20that%20Netanyahu%20is%20a%20tool%20responsible%20for%20propping%20up%20Hamas%20and%20for%20fomenting%20divisions%20in%20Israel%2C%20which%20made%20it%20susceptible%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20column%20is%20thus%20not%20about%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20situation%20but%20reflections%20brought%20on%20by%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20for%20me%2C%20the%20conflict%20has%20led%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20any%20remaining%20delusions%20about%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20liberal%20world%20order.%20The%20basic%20premise%20of%20the%20liberal%20world%20order%20is%20equal%20dignity%20and%20value%20of%20all%20human%20life%20%E2%80%93%20and%20its%20automatic%20extension%2C%20a%20commitment%20to%20truth%20and%20justice.%20However%2C%20everything%20about%20the%20way%20Israel%20is%20going%20about%20its%20campaign%20against%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20the%20de-humaniwing%20rhetoric%2C%20cutting%20off%20water%2C%20power%2C%20and%20other%20supplies%20to%20Gaza%2C%20indiscriminately%20raining%20down%20bombs%20on%20Gaza%20while%20ignoring%20the%20mounting%20civilian%20cost%20%E2%80%93%20goes%20against%20this%20premise.%20But%20what%20has%20put%20paid%20to%20this%20delusion%20is%20not%20just%20what%20Israel%20is%20doing%20but%20the%20endorsement%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions%20by%20the%20apparent%20torchbearers%20of%20liberal%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%2C%20it%20was%20very%20clear%20that%20Putin%20was%20the%20bad%20guy%2C%20the%20entire%20free%20world%20was%20ranged%20against%20Russia%20(with%20some%20abstentions%20but%20certainly%20no%20endorsement).%20But%20now%2C%20not%20only%20is%20the%20world%20leadership%20not%20coming%20together%20as%20one%20to%20demand%20a%20ceasefire%20but%20there%20is%20a%20clampdown%20on%20those%20who%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20152423%2FF80RehHW4AA4TR0.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20152423%2FF80RehHW4AA4TR0.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20152423%2FF80RehHW4AA4TR0-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20152423%2FF80RehHW4AA4TR0-1024x576.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681050%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20damaged%20school%20building%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40UN_SPExperts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conversations%2C%20people%20have%20raised%20similarities%20between%20US%20actions%20in%20Yemen%2C%20Syria%20%E2%80%93%20and%20of%20course%20the%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan.%20There%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20similarities%20but%20there%20are%20also%20significant%20differences%20in%20the%20nature%20and%20scale%20of%20attack%2C%20which%20sets%20the%20present%20moment%20apart.%20Two%20are%20civil%20wars%20with%20foreign%20involvement%20providing%20support%20to%20one%20or%20the%20other%20faction%20in%20a%20proxy%20war%2C%20here%20an%20entire%20population%20is%20besieged.%20In%20the%20others%2C%20there%20was%20at%20least%20some%20pretense%20of%20wanting%20to%20avoid%20civilian%20casualties.%20One%20example%20of%20this%20was%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FHaska_Meyna_wedding_party_airstrike%5C%22%3EAfghanistan%20wedding%20party%20strike%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%20There%20is%20no%20such%20pretense%20here%2C%20Israel%20with%20the%20backing%20of%20the%20United%20States%20is%20just%20brazening%20it%20out.%20Collective%20punishment%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Ede%20facto%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Ede%20jure%3C%2Fem%3E%20policy%20of%20this%20attack%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20recurring%20thought%20has%20been%20how%20the%20distinction%20between%20Hamas%20and%20Gaza%20Palestinians%20has%20been%20elided%20to%20justify%20this%20collective%20punishment.%20The%20fact%20that%20Hamas%20is%20the%20elected%20government%20in%20Gaza%20is%20marshaled%20as%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20collective%20punishment%20of%20Gaza%20Palestinians.%20This%20is%20of%20course%20absurd%20%E2%80%93%20only%20a%20minority%20of%20voters%20actually%20voted%20for%20Hamas%20based%20on%20overall%20turnout%20and%20Hamas%20votes.%20Also%20what%20of%20the%20thousands%20of%20children%20too%20young%20to%20vote%20but%20who%20have%20become%20%E2%80%9Ccollateral%20damage%E2%80%9D%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20destruction%20of%20Gaza%3F%20However%2C%20the%20underlying%20principle%20too%20needs%20to%20be%20called%20out.%20Even%20if%20a%20government%20is%20ostensibly%20very%20popular%2C%20the%20government%20of%20a%20country%20is%20not%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country%20because%20representation%20by%20its%20very%20nature%20is%20flawed%20and%20approximate%2C%20not%20precise.%20In%20fact%2C%20very%20often%20even%20supporters%20of%20a%20regime%20may%20disagree%20with%20the%20regime%20on%20individual%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEffacing%20the%20distinction%20between%20the%20leadership%20and%20the%20people%20leaves%20no%20room%20for%20internal%20differences%2C%20democratic%20dissent%2C%20opposition%2C%20and%20individual%20agency.%20Equally%2C%20this%20glosses%20over%20the%20real%20constraints%20of%20people%20in%20being%20able%20to%20represent%20themselves%20given%20the%20limited%20alternatives%20available%20to%20them.%20This%20mistake%20is%20made%20in%20democratic%20countries%20too%2C%20especially%20by%20liberal%20leaders%20and%20intellectuals%20who%20sometimes%20disparage%20voters%20of%20right-wing%20parties%20as%20racist%20or%20bigoted%20without%20introspecting%20on%20their%20own%20inability%20to%20fully%20understand%20and%2For%20represent%20people%20in%20their%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20corollary%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20liberal%20order%20is%20the%20demise%20of%20old%20uncertainties.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20the%20sense%20that%20outright%20war%20is%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%20or%20more%20generally%20that%20those%20in%20charge%20will%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20%E2%80%93%20but%20that%20it%20is%20no%20longer%20clear%20what%20is%20the%20organising%20principle%20of%20our%20society.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20the%20global%20leadership%20%E2%80%93%20political%2C%20corporate%2C%20media%2C%20and%20other%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20has%20shown%20itself%20to%20be%20insular%2C%20incompetent%2C%20and%20more%20interested%20in%20showmanship%20than%20moving%20issues%20forward%20in%20an%20equitable%20way.%20Charlatans%2C%20extremists%2C%20and%20rank%20opportunists%20have%20captured%20the%20discourse.%20All%20of%20this%20has%20contributed%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20chaos%20%E2%80%93%20what%20Yeats%20wrote%20so%20evocatively%20in%20his%20poem%20%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.poetryfoundation.org%2Fpoems%2F43290%2Fthe-second-coming%5C%22%3EThe%20Second%20Coming%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThings%20fall%20apart%3B%20the%20centre%20cannot%20hold%3B%20Mere%20anarchy%20is%20loosed%20upon%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frgupta.substack.com%2Fp%2Freflections-on-the-israel-palestine%5C%22%3Epiece%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frgupta.substack.com%2Fabout%5C%22%3Eblog%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERuchi%20Gupta%20writes%20about%C2%A0democracy%2C%20tech%2C%20public%20discourse%20%26amp%3B%20contestations%20for%20power%20in%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700052132000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14144837%2FF8Ujv0qWkAA5W3q.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraels-war-on-gaza-affirms-the-collapse-of-liberal-world-order%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20distinction%20between%20Hamas%20and%20Gaza%20Palestinians%20has%20been%20elided%20to%20justify%20this%20collective%20punishment.%20The%20fact%20that%20Hamas%20is%20the%20elected%20government%20in%20Gaza%20is%20being%20marshaled%20as%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20collective%20punishment%20of%20Gaza%20Palestinians%20is%20absurd.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraels-war-on-gaza-affirms-the-collapse-of-liberal-world-order%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20Big%20Bold%20Gambit%20-%20Or%20Is%20It%20Desperation%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBritish%20politics%20has%20once%20again%20taken%20a%20turn%20with%20the%20cabinet%20reshuffle%20ushered%20in%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20this%20week.%20The%20sacking%20of%20Suella%20Braverman%20as%20Home%20Secretary%20and%20the%20return%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20David%20Cameron%20as%20Foreign%20Secretary%20can%20be%20viewed%20both%20as%20a%20desperate%20gambit%20by%20a%20flailing%20leader%20to%20restore%20his%20leadership%20within%20and%20outside%20the%20party%20as%20well%20as%20a%20dramatic%20step%20to%20redraw%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20emerging%20political%20contest%20ahead%20of%20elections%20next%20year.%20Whichever%20way%20you%20look%20at%20it%2C%20the%20spotlight%20is%20now%20back%20on%20Sunak%20as%20he%20comes%20to%20grip%20with%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20decisions%20he%20has%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20home%20secretary%20Braverman%20has%20already%20gone%20on%20the%20record%2C%20dashing%20off%20a%20letter%20to%20Sunak%20telling%20him%20that%20his%20%26quot%3Bplan%20is%20not%20working%26quot%3B%2C%20besides%20accusing%20him%20of%20betraying%20his%20promise%20to%20do%20%26quot%3Bwhatever%20it%20takes%26quot%3B%20to%20stop%20small%20boats%20crossing%20the%20English%20Channel.%20Targeting%20Sunak%20publicly%2C%20she%20has%20written%20%26quot%3BSomeone%20needs%20to%20be%20honest%3A%20your%20plan%20is%20not%20working%2C%20we%20have%20endured%20record%20election%20defeats%2C%20your%20resets%20have%20failed%20and%20we%20are%20running%20out%20of%20time.%20You%20need%20to%20change%20course%20urgently%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20has%20always%20been%20a%20controversial%20politician%20and%20she%20has%20been%20positioning%20herself%20on%20the%20right%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%2C%20emerging%20as%20a%20major%20voice%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20She%20had%20to%20resign%20as%20home%20secretary%20in%20the%20Liz%20Truss%20cabinet%20in%20the%20past%20after%20she%20admitted%20to%20sharing%20confidential%20documents.%20This%20time%20she%20lost%20her%20job%20after%20she%20accused%20the%20Metropolitan%20Police%20of%20bias%20in%20handling%20the%20protests%20in%20an%20article%20for%20the%20Times%20newspaper%20despite%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20asking%20her%20to%20tone%20down%20the%20language.%20Sunak%2C%20who%20has%20had%20to%20rein%20her%20in%20earlier%20too%2C%20perhaps%20found%20that%20his%20leadership%20was%20being%20challenged%20directly%20and%20so%20she%20had%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20thorn%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Sunak.%20In%20her%20letter%2C%20she%20says%20she%20joined%20the%20Sunak%20government%20with%20explicit%20conditionality%2C%20which%20included%20clauses%20like%20assurances%20on%20cutting%20legal%20migration%2C%20and%20guidance%20to%20schools%20on%20protecting%20biological%20sex%20and%20safeguarding%20single-sex%20spaces.%20These%20are%20all%20key%20agenda%20items%20for%20the%20Conservative%20right%20and%20she%20is%20clearly%20trying%20to%20emerge%20their%20undisputed%20leader.%20Sunak%20would%20be%20mistaken%20to%20think%20that%20her%20sacking%20would%20make%20her%20less%20of%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Sunak's%20decision%20to%20let%20her%20go%20and%20bring%20David%20Cameron%2C%20a%20former%20PM%2C%20as%20Foreign%20Secretary%20also%20seems%20to%20be%20about%20the%20political%20positioning%20of%20the%20Tories.%20He%20seems%20to%20be%20underlining%20that%20a%20more%20centrist%20Tory%20Party%20has%20a%20better%20bet%20at%20reelection%20next%20year%20as%20it%20was%20Cameron%20who%20managed%20to%20bring%20the%20Tories%20to%20the%20centre-stage%20and%20make%20them%20winnable%20after%20years%20of%20losing%20against%20a%20Blairite%20Labour%20Party.%20His%20comeback%20is%20not%20as%20historic%20as%20would%20seem%20as%20there%20have%20been%20other%20British%20PMs%20who%20returned%20after%20a%20prime%20ministerial%20turn%20-%20Alec%20Douglas-Home%20and%20Arthur%20Balfour.%20It%20is%20certainly%20dramatic%2C%20though%2C%20as%20no%20one%20had%20any%20indication%20that%20Cameron%20would%20become%20the%20fourth%20Foreign%20Secretary%20in%20as%20many%20years%2C%20through%20the%20House%20of%20Lords.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20this%20is%20creating%20ripples%20both%20within%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20and%20in%20broader%20British%20polity.%20One%20Tory%20backbencher%20has%20already%20submitted%20a%20letter%20of%20no%20confidence%20in%20Sunak%20though%20his%20leadership%20will%20be%20threatened%20only%20if%2053%20MPs%20support%20such%20a%20move.%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20however%2C%20have%20jumped%20on%20Cameron's%20comeback%20asking%20if%20this%20is%20back%20to%20the%20future%20with%20old%20faces%20being%20brought%20back%20when%20Sunak%20had%20promised%20a%20fresh%20start%2C%20especially%20as%20Cameron's%20name%20was%20entangled%20in%20a%20major%20financial%20scandal%20only%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20denying%20the%20fact%20that%20Cameron%20will%20carry%20heft%20in%20the%20world%20of%20diplomacy%20as%20he%20is%20a%20well%20known%20entity%2C%20and%20at%20a%20time%20when%20British%20foreign%20policy%20is%20facing%20major%20challenges%2C%20he%20can%20stabilize%20the%20ship%20somewhat%20just%20by%20his%20presence.%20His%20larger%20foreign%20policy%20legacy%2C%20however%2C%20is%20complicated.%20It%20was%20under%20his%20watch%20that%20the%20referendum%20was%20held%2C%20leading%20to%20Brexit.%20Though%20he%20campaigned%20for%20Britain%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20EU%2C%20the%20consequences%20of%20his%20decision%20to%20call%20for%20a%20referendum%20are%20still%20being%20felt%20in%20Britain%20and%20the%20Europe.%20He%20also%20tried%20to%20envision%20a%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20era%26quot%3B%20of%20closer%20relations%20between%20Britain%20and%20China%2C%20a%20policy%20that%20has%20been%20highly%20problematic%20and%20is%20now%20being%20recrafted.%20In%20the%20Middle%20East%20too%2C%20his%20decisions%20have%20been%20controversial%20from%20Libya%20to%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20India%2C%20though%2C%20Cameron%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20Prime%20Ministers%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20as%20he%20made%20a%20serious%20effort%20to%20jettison%20the%20traditional%20British%20approach%20towards%20the%20subcontinent%20by%20deciding%20to%20deal%20with%20India%20as%20a%20rising%20power%2C%20not%20merely%20as%20a%20South%20Asian%20entity.%20During%20his%20visit%20to%20India%20in%202010%2C%20he%20publicly%20warned%20Pakistan%20against%20promoting%20any%20%26quot%3Bexport%20of%20terror%26quot%3B%2C%20whether%20to%20India%20or%20elsewhere%2C%20and%20said%20it%20must%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20%26quot%3Blook%20both%20ways.%26quot%3B%20Rejecting%20any%20role%20for%20his%20country%20in%20the%20India-Pakistan%20dispute%2C%20he%20proposed%20a%20close%20security%20partnership%20with%20India%2C%20ushering%20in%20a%20new%20momentum%20in%20India-UK%20ties%20that%20continues%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Cameron%20as%20a%20modernizer%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20is%20a%20good%20bet%20for%20Sunak%2C%20the%20fault-lines%20within%20his%20party%20are%20getting%20sharper.%20Braverman's%20exit%20and%20Cameron's%20entry%20is%20unlikely%20to%20change%20the%20dynamic%20within%20the%20Tories.%20Sunak%20has%20a%20tough%2C%20long%20political%20road%20ahead%20to%20navigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHarsh%20V.%20Pant%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20International%20Relations%20at%20King's%20College%20London.%20He%20is%20Vice%20President%20-%20Studies%20and%20Foreign%20Policy%20at%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation%2C%20New%20Delhi.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20Director%20(Honorary)%20of%20the%20Delhi%20School%20of%20Transnational%20Affairs%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700051640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fotenbt1o_rishi-sunak-reuters_625x300_10_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Frishi-sunaks-big-bold-gambit-or-is-it-desperation-4576571%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22British%20politics%20has%20once%20again%20taken%20a%20turn%20with%20the%20cabinet%20reshuffle%20ushered%20in%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20this%20week.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Frishi-sunaks-big-bold-gambit-or-is-it-desperation-4576571%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aria%20Awards%3A%20Troye%20Sivan%20wins%20big%20and%20Kylie%20Minogue%20wins%20with%20Padam%20Padam%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700051559000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FA1BB%2Fproduction%2F_131730414_gettyimages-1794202788.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-67425230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kylie%20Min