rvived%20by%20wife%20Swapna%20Roy%20and%20two%20sons%2C%20Sushanto%20and%20Seemanto.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUntil%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Roy%20was%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20businessmen%20in%20the%20country.%20Mired%20in%20controversies%2C%20facing%20multiple%20regulatory%20and%20legal%20battles%2C%20his%20group%20firms%20accused%20of%20circumventing%20regulations%20with%20Ponzi%20schemes%2C%20in%20the%20recent%20years%2C%20Roy%20was%20only%20known%20to%20allegedly%20having%20duped%20investors%20from%20across%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoy%20made%20a%20modest%20start%20in%201978%20with%20a%20capital%20of%20only%20Rs%202%2C000.%20In%20less%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20he%20was%20able%20to%20build%20Sahara%20India%20over%20the%20decades.%20The%20Group%2C%20as%20per%20the%20claims%20made%20on%20the%20official%20website%2C%20has%209%20crore%20investors%20and%20customers%2C%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20Rs%20259%2C900%20crore%2C%205%2C000%20establishments%20and%2030%2C970%20acres%20of%20land%20bank.%20According%20to%20Reuters%2C%20Sahara%E2%80%99s%20assets%20at%20one%20point%20in%20time%20included%20New%20York%E2%80%99s%20Plaza%20Hotel%20and%20the%20Grosvenor%20House%20in%20London.%20Subrata%20Roy%20was%20once%20also%20a%20co-owner%20of%20the%20former%20Force%20India%20Formula%20One%20team.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMillions%20of%20poor%20Indians%20from%20%3Cem%3Emofussil%3C%2Fem%3E%20parts%20deposited%20money%20in%20his%20company.%20These%20were%20mostly%20illiterate%20with%20zero%20to%20minimum%20access%20to%20formal%20banking%20services.%20The%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20eventually%20stepped%20in%20and%20Roy%E2%80%99s%20companies%20were%20accused%20of%20collection%20of%20over%20Rs%2024%2C000%20crore%20from%20over%20three%20crore%20individuals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202004%2C%20his%20company%20had%20over%201.2%20million%20work%20force%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20only%20second%20to%20the%20Indian%20Railways.%20His%20name%20featured%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ETIME%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%20that%20year.%20His%20business%20%E2%80%93%20spread%20across%20retail%2C%20real%20estate%20and%20financial%20services%20sectors%20soon%20got%20embroiled%20in%20a%20legal%20tussle%20with%20the%20SEBI%20after%20the%20market%20regulator%20in%202011%20ordered%20Sahara%20India%20Real%20Estate%20Corporation%20Ltd%20(SIRECL)%20and%20Sahara%20Housing%20Investment%20Corporation%20Ltd%20(SHICL)%20to%20refund%20the%20money%20raised%20from%20investors%20through%20certain%20bonds%20known%20as%20Optionally%20Fully%20Convertible%20Bonds%20(OFCDs)%20that%20was%20later%20ruled%20to%20be%20illegal.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsaharashri-and-the-supremes%5C%22%3ESaharashri%20and%20the%20Supremes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoy%2C%20however%2C%20with%20his%20close%20political%20connections%2C%20mostly%20with%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20enjoyed%20both%20political%20and%20Bollywood%20clout.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStarting%202010%20began%20his%20slow%20downfall.%20In%202011%2C%20SEBI%20ordered%20two%20Sahara%20Group%20firms%20%E2%80%93%20Sahara%20India%20Real%20Estate%20Corporation%20Ltd%20(SIREL)%20and%20Sahara%20Housing%20Investment%20Corporation%20Ltd%20(SHICL)%20%E2%80%93%20to%20refund%20the%20money%20raised%20from%20nearly%203%20crore%20investors%20through%20certain%20bonds%20known%20as%20Optionally%20Fully%20Convertible%20Bonds%20(OFCDs).%20SEBI%20had%20accused%20his%20two%20companies%20of%20raising%20the%20funds%20by%20violating%20the%20market%20regulator%E2%80%99s%20rules.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202012%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20upheld%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20directions%20asking%20the%20two%20firms%20to%20refund%20the%20money%20collected%20from%20investors%20with%2015%20per%20cent%20interest.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202014%2C%20a%20local%20court%20sent%20Roy%20to%20jail%20for%20not%20paying%20an%20outstanding%20amount%20of%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore.%20His%20release%20was%20conditioned%20on%20return%20of%20Rs%205%2C000%20crore%20in%20cash%20and%20Rs%205%2C000%20crore%20by%20way%20of%20bank%20guarantee.%20Roy%20spent%20two%20years%20in%20jail%2C%20before%20he%20was%20finally%20released%20on%20a%20parole.%20But%20this%20release%20was%20short%20lived.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20soon%20sent%20him%20to%20jail%2C%20only%20for%20him%20to%20be%20later%20released%20on%20bail.%20SEBI%2C%20however%2C%20contested%20the%20bail%20in%202020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20detailed%20investigative%20report%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Fvantage%2Fmodi-receive-over-55-crore-from-sahara-group-chief-minister-gujarat%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epublished%20in%20%3Cem%3ECaravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202016%2C%20journalist%20Paranjoy%20Guha%20Thakurta%20had%20pointed%20to%20over%20Rs%2055%20crore%20from%20the%20Sahara%20Group%20allegedly%20received%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20when%20was%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Gujarat.%20In%20the%20report%2C%20Guha%20Thakurta%20wrote%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20documents%2C%20which%20have%20been%20doing%20the%20rounds%20in%20Delhi%20for%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20suggest%20that%20during%20his%20tenure%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20Modi%E2%80%94along%20with%20a%20number%20of%20important%20politicians%E2%80%94was%20paid%20large%20amounts%20of%20cash%20by%20individuals%20associated%20with%20Subrata%20Roy%2C%20the%20founder-chairman%20of%20the%20Sahara%20India%20Group.%20These%20documents%20also%20suggest%20that%20the%20recipients%20of%20such%20favours%20included%2C%20among%20others%3A%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3B%20Raman%20Singh%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Chhattisgarh%3B%20Shaina%20NC%2C%20the%20treasurer%20for%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20party%20in%20Maharashtra%20and%3B%20Sheila%20Dikshit%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%20of%20Delhi.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20documents%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ECaravan%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20claimed%2C%20bore%20%E2%80%9Can%20uncanny%20resemblance%20to%20the%20infamous%20Jain%20Hawala%20dairies%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201996%2C%20these%20dairies%2C%20which%20came%20into%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20CBI%2C%20indicated%20those%20associated%20with%20businessperson%20Surinder%20Kumar%20Jain%20and%20his%20brother%20had%20made%20payments%20to%20a%20host%20of%20important%20political%20personalities%20such%20as%20L.K.%20Advani%2C%20Madhavrao%20Scindia%2C%20Balram%20Jakhar%2C%20V.C.%20Shukla%2C%20Madan%20Lal%20Khurana%2C%20P.%20Shiv%20Shankar%20and%20Arif%20Mohammed%20Khan%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700044145000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15155744%2FF-8ujsCW4AA6gOA.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fsubrata-roy-sahara-passes-away%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Sahara%20head%20had%20his%20key%20political%20connections%20and%20enjoyed%20significant%20political%20clout.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fsubrata-roy-sahara-passes-away%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22G20%20Virtual%20Summit%3A%20India%20May%20Avoid%20Protest%20During%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20Remarks%2C%20No%20New%20Areas%20of%20Discussion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04141303%2FFjHNMmeakAEkbxa.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20G20%20leaders%20are%20scheduled%20to%20meet%20virtually%20next%20Wednesday%20(November%2022)%2C%20roughly%20a%20week%20before%20India%E2%80%99s%20term%20as%20president%20of%20the%20grouping%20expires%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20virtual%20meeting%E2%80%99s%20agenda%20is%20to%20review%20the%20joint%20declaration%20made%20during%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20September%20and%20follow%20up%20on%20proposals%20made%20there%2C%20media%20reports%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20said%20at%20the%20closing%20ceremony%20of%20the%20summit%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1956014%5C%22%3Emembers%E2%80%99%20responsibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cto%20once%20again%20look%20at%20the%20suggestions%20that%20have%20come%20forward%20%5Band%5D%20to%20see%20how%20their%20progress%20can%20be%20accelerated%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20told%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20while%20such%20a%20review%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20place%20during%20the%20virtual%20meeting%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fg20-virtual-summit-to-take-stock-of-new-delhi-declaration-on-november-22-123111400933_1.html%5C%22%3Enew%20areas%20of%20discussion%20will%20not%20be%20introduced%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20meeting%20will%20allow%20Brazil%2C%20which%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20taking%20over%20as%20G20%20president%20on%20December%201%2C%20to%20take%20up%20the%20concerned%20policy%20initiatives%20next%20year%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20officials%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExternal%20affairs%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20said%20last%20week%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37250%2FTranscript%2Bof%2BWeekly%2BMedia%2BBriefing%2Bby%2Bthe%2BOfficial%2BSpokesperson%2BNovember%2B09%2B2023%5C%22%3Einvitations%20had%20been%20sent%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20all%20leaders%20of%20the%20grouping%20for%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20daily%20added%2C%20citing%20officials%2C%20that%20while%20final%20confirmations%20for%20all%20leaders%E2%80%99%20attendance%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20received%2C%20%E2%80%9Calmost%20all%20leaders%20have%20confirmed%20their%20presence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20of%20leaders%20includes%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20who%20did%20not%20come%20to%20New%20Delhi%20for%20the%20September%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20has%20skipped%20travelling%20to%20such%20summits%20after%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20issued%20an%20arrest%20warrant%20against%20him%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20upcoming%20meeting%20is%20virtual%2C%20Indian%20officials%20are%20pre-empting%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20boycott%20of%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20by%20Western%20leaders%20in%20case%20he%20attends%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Findia-taking-steps-to-avoid-virtual-protests-at-g20-summit%2Farticleshow%2F105192540.cms%5C%22%3Eplanning%20to%20have%20leaders%20appear%20%E2%80%9Csolo%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20screen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20mechanism%20is%20being%20worked%20out%20to%20avoid%20controversy%20over%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20the%20report%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisagreements%20over%20references%20to%20the%20war%20had%20prevented%20joint%20communiques%20after%20all%20ministerial%20meetings%20held%20during%20India%E2%80%99s%20presidency%20prior%20to%20the%20main%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukraine-Russia%20conflict%20as%20well%20as%20the%20ongoing%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20brought%20up%20during%20the%20virtual%20meeting%2C%20media%20reports%20have%20said.%20However%2C%20no%20joint%20statement%20will%20be%20issued%20after%20it%20ends%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20opening%20remarks%20will%20be%20telecast%20live%20but%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20meeting%20will%20not%2C%20media%20reports%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700043358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04141303%2FFjHNMmeakAEkbxa.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-virtual-summit-india-may-avoid-protest-during-putins-remarks-no-new-areas-of-discussion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20presidents%20of%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20may%20attend%20the%20November%2022%20meeting.%20As%20per%20media%20reports%2C%20a%20new%20mechanism%20is%20being%20worked%20out%20to%20avoid%20controversy%20over%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-virtual-summit-india-may-avoid-protest-during-putins-remarks-no-new-areas-of-discussion%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vinod%20Adani%20Among%2066%20Indians%20Who%20Got%20Cyprus%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Golden%20Passport%E2%80%99%20Between%202014%20and%202020%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15150641%2Fimage-1504.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%202014%20and%202020%2C%2066%20Indians%20managed%20to%20obtain%20Cyprus%20passports%20within%20three%20months%20to%20a%20year%2C%20under%20the%20tax%20haven%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20passport%E2%80%9D%20scheme%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20International%20Consortium%20of%20Investigative%20Journalists%20(ICIJ)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexpress-exclusive%2Fvinod-adani-pankaj-oswal-among-66-indians-who-got-golden-passport-9026977%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20part%20of%20Cyprus%20Confidential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fsecrecy-and-no-tax-reason-why-indians-look-at-cyprus-9027035%2F%5C%22%3ECyprus%20Confidential%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20worldwide%20offshore%20probe%20of%203.6%20million%20documents%20in%20English%20and%20Greek%2C%20exposing%20a%20trail%20of%20companies%20established%20in%20Cyprus%20as%20a%20tax%20haven%20by%20global%20elites%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexpress-exclusive%2Fcracking-cyprus-confidential-eu-state-gave-investors-tax-haven-secrecy-and-a-golden-passport-9026642%2F%5C%22%3ERussian%20oligarchs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CCyprus%20Investment%20Programme%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20passport%E2%80%9D%20scheme%20was%20launched%20in%202007.%20It%20enabled%20financially%20prominent%20individuals%20to%20obtain%20Cypriot%20citizenship%2C%20thereby%20attracting%20foreign%20direct%20investments%20into%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%2066%20Indians%20who%20got%20their%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20passport%E2%80%9D%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fvinod-gautam-adani-u-turn%5C%22%3EVinod%20Adani%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Gautam%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20elder%20brother%20who%20came%20under%20spotlight%20in%20Hindenburg%20Research%E2%80%99s%20investigation%3B%20Pankaj%20Oswal%2C%20chairman%20and%20founder%20of%20Burrup%20Holdings%20Limited%2C%20and%20real%20estate%20baron%20Surendra%20Hiranandani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20European%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20website%2C%20Cyprus%20repealed%20its%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20passport%E2%80%9D%20scheme%20and%20stopped%20receiving%20new%20applications%20on%20November%201%2C%202020.%20However%2C%20it%20continued%20to%20process%20pending%20applications.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20European%20Commission%20decided%20to%20send%20a%20reasoned%20opinion%20to%20Cyprus%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fcommission%2Fpresscorner%2Fdetail%2Fen%2Finf_21_2743%5C%22%3EJune%209%2C%202021%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Since%20then%2C%20Cyprus%20stopped%20processing%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20scrapped%20due%20to%20alleged%20misuse%20and%20for%20allowing%20persons%20with%20criminal%20charges%2C%20dubious%20character%20and%20PEPs%20(politically%20exposed%20persons)%20to%20acquire%20Cyprus%20passports%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENames%20of%20a%20total%20of%2083%20individuals%20were%20flagged%20for%20review%20and%20possible%20revocation.%20A%20majority%20of%20them%20were%20earlier%20citizens%20of%20Russia%20and%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data%2C%20most%20were%20marked%20for%20applications%20bearing%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20statement%20by%20the%20investors%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20daily%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Commission%20appointed%20by%20the%20Attorney%20General%20of%20Cyprus%2C%20Georgios%20Savvides%2C%20in%20September%202020%20and%20headed%20by%20retired%20Supreme%20Court%20Chairman%2C%20Myron%20Nicolatos%2C%20made%20the%20list%20of%20these%20possible%20revocations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Cyprus%20government%20has%20not%20yet%20officially%20revealed%20how%20many%20of%20those%20under%20the%20scanner%20had%20their%20Cypriot%20citizenships%20revoked%2C%20the%20daily%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERevocations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20there%20is%20only%20one%20Indian%20on%20the%20list%20of%20proposed%20revocations%20of%20Cypriot%20passports%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Fnsel-case-ed-attaches-defaulters-property-in-dubai%2Farticle65523301.ece%5C%22%3EAnubhav%20Aggarwal%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20businessman%20whose%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20passport%E2%80%9D%20was%20approved%20within%20four%20months%20on%20November%202%2C%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nicolatos%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20inquiry%20report%20states%20that%20Aggarwal%20was%20implicated%20in%20the%20National%20Spot%20Exchange%20Limited%20(NSEL)%20scam%20and%20that%20he%20failed%20to%20mention%20his%20links%20with%20the%20suspect%20companies%20in%20his%20application%20for%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20%E2%80%9Ckey%20accused%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Rs%203%2C600%20crore%20NSEL%20scam%2C%20Aggarwal%20faced%20arrest%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20in%20August%202020.%20In%20June%202020%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20seized%20his%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwal%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20only%20Indian%20obtaining%20Cypriot%20citizenship%20under%20the%20now-defunct%20investment%20scheme%2C%20despite%20legal%20issues%20with%20Indian%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENesamanimaran%20Muthu%2C%20better%20known%20as%20MGM%20Maran%2C%20a%20Tamil%20Nadu-based%20businessman%20and%20former%20chairman%20of%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Mercantile%20Bank%20Limited%2C%20acquired%20Cypriot%20citizenship%20in%202016.%20His%20application%20was%20cleared%20in%20just%20two%20months.%20In%202017%2C%20his%20two%20children%20also%20got%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20the%20ED%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbfsi.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findustry%2Fed-attaches-assets-worth-rs-205-36-cr-of-chennai-based-firm%2F96538226%5C%22%3Eattached%3C%2Fa%3E%20assets%20worth%20Rs%20200%20crores%20of%20his%20Maran%E2%80%99s%20company%2C%20Agrifurane%20Industries%20Private%20Limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20probe%20agency%20had%20issued%20a%20media%20release%20saying%20that%20assets%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Rs%20293%20crore%20had%20been%20attached%20by%20them%20since%20an%20equivalent%20foreign%20investment%20had%20been%20made%20by%20Maran%20in%20two%20companies%20in%20Singapore%20without%20approval%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20also%20mentioned%20Maran%E2%80%99s%20Cypriot%20citizenship%20in%20an%20official%20release.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20order%20to%20escape%20the%20reach%20of%20Indian%20laws%2C%20MGM%20Maran%20surrendered%20his%20Indian%20citizenship.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20it%20was%20also%20found%20that%20MGM%20Maran%20also%20started%20transferring%20his%20wealth%20from%20India%20to%20overseas%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20the%20same%20out%20of%20reach%20of%20the%20Indian%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20in%20the%20garb%20of%20overseas%20direct%20investments%20from%20Southern%20Agrifurane%20Industries%20Private%20Limited%20(his%20flagship%20company)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ED%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Cyprus%20Confidential%20investigation%20by%20OCCRP%20and%20other%20media%20partners%2C%20the%20Cyprus%20Ministry%20of%20Interior%20said%20that%20they%20have%20decided%20on%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20deprivation%20of%20citizenship%20of%20233%20individuals%20and%20of%20them%2C%2068%20individuals%20are%20investors%20and%20165%20are%20family%20members%20of%20the%20investors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAllegations%20over%20tax%20evasion%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20January%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhindenburgresearch.com%2Fadani%2F%5C%22%3EHindenburg%20Research%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailed%20Vinod%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20offshore%20holdings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%2C%20which%20included%20downloading%20and%20cataloguing%20the%20entire%20Mauritius%20corporate%20registry%2C%20uncovered%20that%20Vinod%20Adani%2C%20through%20several%20close%20associates%2C%20manages%20a%20vast%20labyrinth%20of%20offshore%20shell%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20r